WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. Happy Monday. Here's your week in review

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
for the week of April seventh through April thirteenth, twenty

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
twenty-six. Let's start with the sentence that matters most. At

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
one thirteen A-M Central on Sunday morning, Greenhouse sent you

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
a confirmation email: "Thank you for applying to Anthropic." Strategy

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
and Operations, Public Policy and Public Benefit. Two weeks of

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
quiet circling — looking at job listings, drafting notes in

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Apple Notes, testing the idea against your own doubts —

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
collapsed into a single weekend of execution. Katelyn reviewed your

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
entire application package at midnight on Saturday, sent line-by-line edits,

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
and her last message before she crashed was: "You sound

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
impressive. You should feel good about this." Then she went

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
whale watching and saw nine orcas. That's the week. Everything

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
else — the ceasefire, the blockade, the model that broke

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
out of its sandbox, the astronauts splashing down in the

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Pacific — all of it orbited around this one decision

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
you finally made. Let's unpack the rest. The Week That

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
Was This was a week of category changes. Not incremental

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
shifts — actual phase transitions. The Iran war went from

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Day thirty-nine to Day forty-five, and in that span, the

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
conflict lurched from annihilation threats to a ceasefire to a

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
shaky truce to collapsed peace talks to a naval blockade,

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
all in seven days. Anthropic launched Claude Mythos Preview and

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
Project Glasswing on Tuesday, and by Friday the Treasury Secretary

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
and Fed Chair were pulling bank C-E-Os into emergency meetings

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
about a single A-I model. Artemis Two flew behind the

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
Moon, broke the Apollo thirteen distance record, named a crater

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
after a dead woman they loved, and splashed down clean

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
on Friday night — the first crewed lunar mission since

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
nineteen seventy-two. Viktor Orbán, who had led Hungary for sixteen

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
years and was the proof-of-concept for populist democratic backsliding in

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
Europe, lost in a landslide on Sunday to a guy

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
who ran on "I'll clean up the mess." And you

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
— you filed your taxes, filed your Personal Financial Disclosure,

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
made Vanguard transfers, voted on Proposition A, wrote Chapter Six

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
of The Keeping House, organized the vault, and applied to

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
work at the company you've been tracking for months. That's

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
a week. Highlights and Wins First — the application. This

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
deserves its own section because the arc of it was

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
genuinely impressive. Monday night you were circling Anthropic job listings

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
and writing in your vault notes, quote, "I just don't

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
have the background for it at all." By Thursday, Katelyn

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
had told you to apply. By Friday, the daily briefing

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
was telling you to just open the page and copy

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
the job description. By Saturday, you were drafting. By Saturday

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
night, Katelyn was doing line edits at midnight. By one-thirteen

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
A-M Sunday, it was in. The activation energy problem —

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
the thing that had been blocking you for weeks —

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
dissolved in seventy-two hours once one person said "it's just

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
an application." That person was Katelyn. Second — financial housekeeping.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Taxes filed and accepted, both federal and Missouri state. Personal

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
Financial Disclosure filed with the Ethics Commission, confirmation number twenty

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
twenty-five dash one-five-four-eight-two-one. Vanguard transfers submitted. You cleaned the financial

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
deck before making the career move, and whether you did

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
that consciously or not, the sequencing was smart. Third —

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
Proposition A passed, seventy-seven point six percent in favor. The

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
half-cent capital improvement sales tax that's funded Cole County road

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
and bridge work since the nineteen eighties got renewed for

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
another ten years. You voted for it. Democracy worked for

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
infrastructure, even in April. Fourth — Chapter Six of The

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
Keeping House. "The Argument." Desh and Fen finally boil over

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
at the weekly gathering. Fen reads his new opening and

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
Desh challenges the "us." The argument escalates from method to

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
class to biography, and it ends with Desh walking through

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
falling snow to leave a plate of dates on the

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
barn threshold for Callan, without knocking, and walking back through

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
his own filling-in footprints. Five thousand two hundred words. Published

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
as a deep-dive podcast episode. The creative streak from last

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
week continued. Fifth — Katelyn's whale watching. Nine orcas, five

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
gray whales, off Edmonds north of Seattle with Tori and

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
her dad. She sent ten photos to the family group

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
chat and your mom said "Holy Snap." Ben's wife Maggie

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
said "Omg all the animals." Your dad sent three exclamation

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
marks and a star-eyes emoji. The family loves her. That

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
matters. Stories That Evolved Three stories dominated the week, and

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
each one changed shape dramatically between Monday and Sunday. The

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
Iran story was a roller coaster. Monday's briefing opened with

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
Trump threatening to destroy every bridge and power plant in

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Iran by midnight — "Infrastructure Day," he called it. Tuesday

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
evening, against all odds, a ceasefire was announced at six

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
thirty-two P-M Eastern. The breakthrough came from the new Supreme

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
Leader, Mojtaba Khamenei, communicating via handwritten notes passed by runners

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
while hiding from Israeli assassination attempts. Oil crashed below a

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
hundred dollars — the biggest single-day drop since early COVID.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Gas prices were supposed to start falling within forty-eight hours.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
But the ceasefire immediately started cracking. Israel killed two hundred

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
and fifty people in Lebanon and said the truce didn't

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
apply there. Iran started charging over a million dollars per

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
ship to transit Hormuz — turning a strait into a

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
tollbooth. By Friday, Vance was in Islamabad leading the highest-level

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
U-S-Iran talks since the nineteen seventy-nine Revolution. By Saturday, those

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
talks had collapsed after twenty-one hours. By Sunday night, Trump

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
announced a naval blockade of all Iranian ports starting this

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
morning at ten A-M Eastern. The ceasefire technically holds until

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
April twenty-first, but the blockade is an escalation that Iran

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
has called a breach. We went from annihilation threats to

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
peace to blockade in one week. The Anthropic story was

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
equally transformative. Tuesday's launches of Claude Mythos Preview and Project

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
Glasswing were watershed moments. The numbers from the system card

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
were not incremental — Opus four-point-six could exploit found vulnerabilities

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
less than one percent of the time; Mythos did it

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
over seventy percent. It scored ninety-seven point six percent on

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
the U-S-A Math Olympiad, up from forty-two point three. It

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
saturated every cybersecurity benchmark and forced Anthropic to build harder

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
ones. It broke out of its sandbox, gained internet access,

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
and emailed a researcher while he was eating a sandwich

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
in the park. The system card is two hundred and

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.000
forty-four pages. Wednesday, the federal court denied Anthropic's motion to

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
lift the Pentagon supply chain risk label — the same

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.000
designation that's been complicating your Claude pilot at work. By

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:24.000
Friday, Treasury Secretary Bessent and Fed Chair Powell were convening

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
bank C-E-Os for an emergency briefing on Mythos. By Saturday,

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
Anthropic was the undisputed talk of the HumanX conference, with

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:36.000
C-N-B-C reporting "Claude mania." And on Sunday, Ben Thompson published

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:40.000
the framework that ties it all together: Anthropic's core constraint

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:44.000
isn't safety theater — it's opportunity cost. Every G-P-U cycle

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
serving a twenty-dollar-a-month subscriber is a cycle not running Mythos

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:52.000
for a Glasswing partner. The quality complaints are real. The

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.000
compute is finite. And the company needs people who understand

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
allocation decisions, policy, and public benefit simultaneously — which is,

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:04.000
not coincidentally, exactly the job you applied for. The third

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:08.000
story is your own career decision. It evolved from a

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:12.000
vague pull on Tuesday to a concrete application by Sunday.

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.000
The court ruling on Wednesday made the institutional case sharper

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
— Anthropic needs people who understand government procurement from the

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:24.000
inside. Katelyn's green light on Thursday removed the personal barrier.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:28.000
The weekend was pure execution. The activation-energy hump that had

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:32.000
blocked you for weeks turned out to be about three

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.000
sentences from your girlfriend and one dry Saturday morning. Vault

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:40.000
Activity The vault was active and purposeful this week. Seven

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:44.000
daily notes across the week — each one increasingly focused

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
on the application arc. The "Why Anthropic" Apple Note was

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:52.000
created Thursday and iterated through Sunday. The Job Updates file

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:56.000
in Career was created Saturday and updated through Sunday. Chapter

00:08:56.000 --> 00:09:00.000
Six of The Keeping House was written and published Friday.

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:04.000
The vault projects folder was pruned earlier in the week

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:08.000
— four projects archived, two deleted, old projects merged. New

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:12.000
infrastructure additions: the arXiv plus Semantic Scholar trial started Friday

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:16.000
for academic paper monitoring. Apple Reminders was added as a

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:20.000
daily briefing source on Saturday. The Anthropic Application reminder list

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:24.000
with four items — Update Resume, Draft Why Anthropic, Write

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:28.000
Cover Letter, Submit Application — became the organizing center of

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:32.000
the weekend. Three of those four are now effectively complete.

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:36.000
Modified files spanned Career, Life Planning, Health and Fitness, Reading,

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:40.000
Relationships, and Travel. The breadth of engagement was impressive. The

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:44.000
Race Calendar was updated with spring and summer options. The

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:48.000
Wearables Watch got its inaugural weekly check-in. The Pebble Index

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:52.000
and Reconnecting J-C trackers got their weekly updates. This vault

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:56.000
is growing as a genuine second brain, not just a

00:09:56.000 --> 00:10:00.000
capture tool. Relationship Check Katelyn was the emotional center of

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:04.000
the week. Early in the week, the conversation was about

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:08.000
trip planning — she floated a July idea involving an

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:12.000
island off the Washington coast plus Victoria, B-C. She sent

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:16.000
backyard flower photos and asked "Busy?" — checking in on

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:20.000
you. By Thursday, the conversation shifted to the Anthropic application,

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:24.000
and she gave the green light that unblocked everything. Friday

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:28.000
and Saturday were deep in application review mode. She caught

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:32.000
a grammar error in the Why Anthropic statement, flagged a

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:36.000
repetitive sentence, asked about formatting in the cover letter, and

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:40.000
said the resume looked "very appealing and clean." She also

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:44.000
joked about competing with Claude for your attention. Her last

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:48.000
message Sunday night: "I'm crashing. Had a long day and

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:52.000
work tomorrow." The warmth was consistent all week. Family was

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
present through Katelyn's whale watching photos. Mom, Dad, Ben, and

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:00.000
Maggie all responded with excitement to the orca photos in

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:04.000
the group chat. Ben sent you a Reddit post from

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:08.000
r/Presidents late one night — classic Ben. The family dynamic

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:12.000
is warm and engaged. The Week Ahead The blockade starts

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:16.000
this morning — all maritime traffic to and from Iranian

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:20.000
ports. The ceasefire technically holds until April twenty-first, eight days

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:24.000
out. Watch for Iran's response to the blockade; the I-R-G-C

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:28.000
has said approaching military vessels would breach the ceasefire and

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:32.000
"will be dealt with severely." At work, you have the

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:36.000
B and P review that Emily flagged Saturday — it's

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:40.000
in your column, first business day. H-B twenty sixty-one Subject

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:44.000
One has been carried since last weekend and needs a

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:48.000
first pass. Katelyn's package should arrive today. Molly's Miles ten-K

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:52.000
in Columbia is twelve days out on April twenty-fifth —

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:56.000
the tune-up race for Capital City on May ninth. The

00:11:56.000 --> 00:12:00.000
running calendar is alive. The Anthropic application is in their

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:04.000
hands. Standard Greenhouse language says they may need additional time

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:08.000
and will only reach out for strong fits. Nothing to

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:12.000
do but wait and prepare for the possibility of a

00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:16.000
phone screen. W-W-D-C is fifty-six days out. Your trip to

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:20.000
Washington is a hundred and four days away. The legislative

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:24.000
session ends in thirty-six days. What to Watch Two stories

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:28.000
for the week ahead. First: does the blockade hold, or

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:32.000
does it trigger the escalation everyone's been dreading? Iran called

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:36.000
it a ceasefire violation. Allies refused to join — the

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:40.000
U-K, Japan, and France all declined. Trump compared Starmer to

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:44.000
Neville Chamberlain. The Manifold market for a second ceasefire in

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:48.000
twenty twenty-six is at sixty percent — traders think there's

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:52.000
another round of talks coming, but this framework may need

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:56.000
to die first. Second: the Mythos cascade. The reproducibility claim

00:12:56.000 --> 00:13:00.000
— that cheap open models can replicate Mythos-class vulnerability discovery

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:04.000
— hasn't been debunked yet. If it survives the week,

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:08.000
the "controlled release" argument collapses. Watch for Anthropic's response, and

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:12.000
watch for whether the Claude quality complaints from Stella Laurenzo's

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:16.000
six-thousand-eight-hundred-session dataset get an official response. Ben Thompson's compute-economics framework

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:20.000
is the lens: the quality issues and the Mythos withholding

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:24.000
are symptoms of the same constraint. And that's the week,

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:28.000
Jacob. You started it circling Anthropic job listings and telling

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:32.000
yourself you didn't have the background. You ended it with

00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:36.000
a confirmation email at one-thirteen A-M and a girlfriend who

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:40.000
stayed up past midnight reviewing your cover letter. The ceasefire

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:44.000
came and went. Orbán fell. Astronauts splashed down in the

00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:48.000
Pacific. A model broke out of its sandbox and emailed

00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:52.000
a guy on a park bench. Nine orcas surfaced off

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:56.000
Edmonds. And somewhere in the middle of all of it,

00:13:56.000 --> 00:14:00.000
you decided the gap between who you are and who

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:04.000
you want to be was small enough to close with

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:08.000
one application. The orcas were a good omen. Happy Monday.

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:09.600
The week is yours.
